article_title: Muhammad Cartoon Contest Gunman Wasn’t Seen as Pressing Threat
article_text:
One of the gunmen in the failed attack on a Texas contest to draw caricatures of the Prophet Muhammad was under investigation but wasn’t viewed as an immediate threat by federal officials, who on Tuesday explored links to Islamic State after the militant group claimed responsibility for the incident.
